The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring the third Saturday of May as Armed Forces Day. The proclamation recognizes the courage and patriotism of the members of the Armed Forces, who represent America as ambassadors of its principles. It emphasizes the importance of supporting and providing resources to the service members and their families. The proclamation also calls upon Americans to display the flag of the United States at their homes on Armed Forces Day and encourages them to learn more about military service and volunteer at organizations that support the troops.